postcontent: The new Chiappa Rhino has revolutionized the revolver with a patented design that tames the prehistoric characteristic  that most revolvers possess. The new Chiappa Rhino barrel is aligned with the bottom most chamber which is the key component to Rhino's tame characteristics. The position of the barrel lowers the center of gravity and yields a centerline of the bore more in line with the shooter's arm allowing for the most natural "point ability" while engaging a target. This characteristic also drastically reduces both recoil and muzzle flip which insures subsequent shots to be on target faster than ever before. The reduction of the recoil allows for the use of ultra light alloys to be used in the construction of the Rhino minimizing any adverse effect. The flat sided cylinder design of the Rhino reduces the typical revolver profile allowing greater concealment. With choices from 2" to 6" barrel lengths and sight options, the Rhino is truly a multipurpose handgun capable of reliable defensive duty, scoring ten rings, and taking game. title: For Trade:  Yugo SKS - All-Matching w/ Tek Sights & 2 30rd Mags
postcontent:
Up for trade is a Yugo SKS, all matching #'s, with attached Tek-Sights and 2 30rd mags.

Appears to be in good shape overall, with a few knicks here and there.  Finish on grenade launcher mount is stripped, though I've got it tapped and ready for removal if you'd like to attach a muzzle break.  

Tek sights make this a SWEET shooter; adds ~11" of sight picture, makes it much easier to reach out and touch a target at 100+ yrds.  Easily removable for restoration to stock sights (though from a shooting standpoint I don't see a good reason to do so).  

Rifling is damn near perfect, and overall internals seem to be in very good shape.  I've shot ~200 rds with constant cleanings, and previous owner seems to have taken great care of her as well.  Detail strips on my end show near-mint internals.

Has spring-loaded firing pin to avoid slamfires, and have had some cleanup work on the trigger so she's as close to "glass rod" as you're going to find in an SKS.

Overall, great gun in great shape, and a SWEET shooter.

title: For Sale:  AK-47 SAR-1 & (5) Thirty Round Magazines
postcontent:
Looking to move my SAR-1 AK-47 and Magazines.

Bought new in 2001 - less than 1000 rds through it.
Rifle built in 2001 using the original trigger groups, not the cheap tapco groups in later imports.
Had a gunsmith deburr some internals to smooth out and lighten the trigger pull - 
Now a very nice (light) trigger that allows bump firing, or burst firing from the shoulder if you wish.

Comes with 5 thirty round magazines and speed loader. (4 steel, 1 poly, all with bolt hold open device - very rare in AK Mags)

 - Romanian Red Bakelite Pistol grip and stock black pistol grip
 - Muzzle Break - not yet installed
 - Chrome lined barrel
 - PU scope mount ready for optics

The SAR is a true AKM clone.  Unlike the Wasr which is a sporter designed to take single stack magazines and them drilled our to fit larger mags, the SAR is built to take hi cap mags and holds the mags in place with dimples on the receiver like an AKM.  This means the SAR will accept any mag and any Ammo.   The SAR also contains the "Third Pin" in the trigger group assembly so it is ready to convert to a full auto trigger group if you wish to do that in the future.
 - The Wasr is a designed sporter adapted to become an assault style weapon
 - The SAR is a military full auto adapted to semi auto civilian use

Really nice rifle - just have nowhere to shoot it anymore.
